index.html.title: VisualDS
index.html.name: VisualDS
index.html.summary: A javascript library for code driven visualization of data structures and algorithms.

Pointer.html.title: Pointer
Pointer.html.name: Pointer
Pointer.html.description: This class represents a visual array index variable. DO NOT create an object of this using the constructor. Always use getPointer() method of vArray to get an object of this.

Pointer.html#pointee.title: pointee :vArray
Pointer.html#pointee.name: pointee
Pointer.html#pointee.description: The vArray object this Pointer object will point to

Pointer.html#index.title: index :number
Pointer.html#index.name: index
Pointer.html#index.description: The index at which this pointer is pointing to. This is the index that changes when user makes changes.

Pointer.html#drawIndex.title: drawIndex :number
Pointer.html#drawIndex.name: drawIndex
Pointer.html#drawIndex.description: The index at which this pointer is drawn. This is the index that changes when animations are scheduled.

Pointer.html#label.title: label :string
Pointer.html#label.name: label
Pointer.html#label.description: The label to show below this pointer

Pointer.html#stateMachine.title: stateMachine :StateMachine
Pointer.html#stateMachine.name: stateMachine
Pointer.html#stateMachine.description: The state machine to handle the states of this pointer. Initial state is idle.

Pointer.html#getIndex.title: getIndex()
Pointer.html#getIndex.name: getIndex
Pointer.html#getIndex.description: Get the current index value of the pointer

Pointer.html#isOutOfBound.title: isOutOfBound()  {boolean}
Pointer.html#isOutOfBound.name: isOutOfBound
Pointer.html#isOutOfBound.description: Check whether the current index value is out of the bounds of vArray

Pointer.html#move.title: move( change )
Pointer.html#move.name: move
Pointer.html#move.description: Moves the pointer by the specified amount of change in index value.

Pointer.html#moveTo.title: moveTo( index )
Pointer.html#moveTo.name: moveTo
Pointer.html#moveTo.description: Moves the pointer to a specified index

Pointer.html#increment.title: increment()
Pointer.html#increment.name: increment
Pointer.html#increment.description: Increment the index of pointer by 1 Same as calling move(1)

Pointer.html#decrement.title: decrement()
Pointer.html#decrement.name: decrement

Pointer.html#highlight.title: highlight( color )
Pointer.html#highlight.name: highlight
Pointer.html#highlight.description: Hightlights the element where this pointer is pointing. No effect if isOutOfBound() returns true.

Pointer.html#unhighlight.title: unhighlight()
Pointer.html#unhighlight.name: unhighlight

Pointer.html#remove.title: remove()
Pointer.html#remove.name: remove
Pointer.html#remove.description: Removes this pointer from the drawing pool. Also, no animations can be queued after this feom this pointer.

vArray.html.title: vArray
vArray.html.name: vArray
vArray.html.description: This class represents a visual array. It can be an array of anything, i.e string, number, custom objects, etc. The only restriction is that the class, whose objects are in the array, should have a toString() method that returns what needs to be written in the visualized object in the visualized array. It may be a single line text, or a multiline text. If just passing array of numbers, or strings, then no need to worry about toString since it is there by default in these inbuilt classes. With its pushBack(), popBack(), pushFront(), popFront() methods, it can be used as a stack or queue as well.

vArray.html#data.title: data :Array.<any>
vArray.html#data.name: data
vArray.html#data.description: This is the actual data inside the array, that changes with the synchronous code written by user.

vArray.html#label.title: label :string
vArray.html#label.name: label
vArray.html#label.description: The label to draw above the array

vArray.html#drawData.title: drawData :Array.<vElement>
vArray.html#drawData.name: drawData
vArray.html#drawData.description: This is the copy utilized for drawing on every frame. It changes asynchronously, as and when animations related to the varray object are selected from the animation queue.

vArray.html#pointers.title: pointers :Array.<Pointer>
vArray.html#pointers.name: pointers
vArray.html#pointers.description: The list of pointers (index variables) that point to elements of this array. Required, because along with the array itself, these also need to be drawn and updated on every frame.

vArray.html#boxWidth.title: boxWidth :number
vArray.html#boxWidth.name: boxWidth
vArray.html#boxWidth.description: Width of a single element drawn

vArray.html#boxHeight.title: boxHeight :number
vArray.html#boxHeight.name: boxHeight
vArray.html#boxHeight.description: Height of a single element drawn

vArray.html#stateMachine.title: stateMachine :StateMachine
vArray.html#stateMachine.name: stateMachine
vArray.html#stateMachine.description: To manage the animation via states

vArray.html#get.name: get

vArray.html#pushBack.name: pushBack

vArray.html#popFront.title: popFront()

vArray.html#unhighlightRange.description: Unhighlight a range of indices, start and end are both inclusive.

vArray.html#getPointer.name: getPointer

vElement.html.title: vElement
vElement.html.name: vElement
vElement.html.description: This is that class that encapsulates any object that is to be drawn. It may be number, string, or even a custom Student object, provided it has a toString() overridden that returns the text representation of the object. User of the framework may want to create individual objects of this class that would be drawn (with isSlave = false) and managed by the animator directly. This is useful when the user wants to show a single object on the screen., for example, a number or a string. or the user may not use this at all, instead the user may use higher level classes such as vArray which internally uses vElement objects (with isSlave = true).

vElement.html#val.title: val :*
vElement.html#val.name: val
vElement.html#val.description: The object encapsulated. This gets updated along with the synchronous code (code written by the user).

vElement.html#drawVal.title: drawVal :*
vElement.html#drawVal.name: drawVal
vElement.html#drawVal.description: The object utilized to draw. This gets updated as and when the animation related to any updation is executed by animator.

vElement.html#label.title: label :string
vElement.html#label.name: label
vElement.html#label.description: The label/name that is to be displayed when drawing this vElement

vElement.html#color.title: color :string
vElement.html#color.name: color
vElement.html#color.description: The color of the box in which to display the object

vElement.html#font.title: font :string
vElement.html#font.name: font
vElement.html#font.description: The font style utilized to write the toString() text of the drawVal in the box

vElement.html#labelFont.title: labelFont :string
vElement.html#labelFont.name: labelFont
vElement.html#labelFont.description: The font style utilized to write the label

vElement.html#text.title: text :Array.<string>
vElement.html#text.name: text
vElement.html#text.description: The text representation of the drawVal object, as an array of strings which are to be drawn on separate lines

vElement.html#stateMachine.title: stateMachine :StateMachine
vElement.html#stateMachine.name: stateMachine
vElement.html#stateMachine.description: The state machine to manage the states of vElement. Initial state is idle.

vElement.html#setVal.title: setVal( val, highlight )
vElement.html#setVal.name: setVal
vElement.html#setVal.description: Sets the new value of the encapsulated object

vElement.html#getVal.title: getVal()
vElement.html#getVal.name: getVal
vElement.html#getVal.description: Get the current value of the encapsulated object

vElement.html#highlight.title: highlight( color )
vElement.html#highlight.name: highlight
vElement.html#highlight.description: Hightlight the vElement with the given color. Registers the animation for changing the color of the box

vElement.html#unhighlight.title: unhighlight()
vElement.html#unhighlight.name: unhighlight
vElement.html#unhighlight.description: Unhightlights the vElement Registers the animation for changing the color of the box to default color

vElement.html#remove.name: remove
